#### When to Use Relational vs Document Databases

| Use Case | Relational (PostgreSQL) | Document (MongoDB) |
|----------|------------------------|-------------------|
| **Complex relationships** | ‚úÖ Excellent (JOINs) | ‚ùå Manual references |
| **Data consistency** | ‚úÖ ACID guarantees | ‚ö†Ô∏è Eventual consistency |
| **Fixed schema** | ‚úÖ Enforced | ‚ùå Schema-less |
| **Transactions** | ‚úÖ Native support | ‚ö†Ô∏è Limited |
| **Aggregations** | ‚úÖ Powerful SQL | ‚úÖ Aggregation pipeline |
| **Scalability** | ‚ö†Ô∏è Vertical (bigger servers) | ‚úÖ Horizontal (more servers) |

**Next Photon's Needs**:
- ‚úÖ Complex relationships (Learner ‚Üí Guardian ‚Üí ECM ‚Üí Educator ‚Üí Session)
- ‚úÖ Data consistency (payment records, attendance, grades)
- ‚úÖ Transactions (book session + charge payment + notify user)
- ‚úÖ Fixed schema (7 user roles with specific fields)

**Verdict**: PostgreSQL is the perfect fit!

